      • getNavigationCriteria

        public abstract NavigationCriteria getNavigationCriteria(NavigationCriteria nc,
                                                         EquivalenceLink link,
                                                         boolean fetchDownstream)
                                                  throws WTException
        Method to get new NavigationCriteria to find object to next level.

        Make the NavigationCriteria object final in delegate so that original navigation criteria obejct doesn't gets modified or first make deep copy of navigation criteria.

        Supported API: true
        Parameters:
        nc - Original NavigationCriteria
        link - EquivalenceLink from which further links will be searched
        fetchDownstream - whether new NavigationCriteria is required to find upstream network or downstream network
        Returns:
        new NavigationCriteria to find further links
        Throws:
        WTException

      • continueToNext

        public abstract boolean continueToNext(EquivalenceNetwork currentNetwork,
                                       boolean isDownstream)
        Method which will determine whether to proceed finding next level network

        EquivalenceNetwork object has all the links in the current network. One can use this information to build the logic while customizing the delegate.

        Supported API: true
        Parameters:
        currentNetwork - current EquivalenceNetwork object
        isDownstream - whether method called to find upstream network or downstream
        Returns:
        true or false to find further network. default true
